organization.description: The Center for Family and Child Enrichment is a private, nonprofit, community-based organization that serves children in foster care who have been abused, neglected and/or abandoned; children with severe emotional disturbances and in need of mental health care; children in the custody of parents or relatives who are chronic runaways and/or are ungovernable; and children who come to this country without parents or guardians (unaccompanied minors). Our mission is to enrich, strengthen, preserve, restore, and empower children and families in a culturally diverse community
organization.name: CENTER FOR FAMILY AND CHILD ENRICHMENT, INC.
